===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-æʃt|-æʃt]]

===Verb form===
'''dashed'''
# Past tense and [[past participle]] of '''to [[dash]]'''.

===Adjective===
'''dashed'''

#Of a line, made up of short lines with small gaps between each one and the next.
#(''UK, informal'') A [[euphemism]] for '''[[damned]]'''.
#:''It's a dashed shame that Tarquin failed all his A-levels &mdash; we were hoping to get him into Oxford.''

====Usage notes====
*'''Dashed''' in the sense of "damned" is considered to be upper-class or somewhat old-fashioned.

====Synonyms====
*(''line''): [[broken]]
*(''damned''): <!--note: these are euphemisms for "damned"-->[[darned]] (''especially US'')

